1.title: Game of Drones

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: Can Kevin and Grant build an amphibious motorcycle that drives on the water? In an ultra-scientific mini-golf competition, who can make the most holes-in-one? Plus, the guys live out a real-life video game when they build and race virtual reality drones.

2.title: Monster Truck Golf Cart

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

2.plot: Kevin and Grant become monsters of the fairway when they turn a golf cart into a monster truck. The guys take on the science of Spider-Man when they engineer a way to scale a 50-foot wall. And they turn power tools into high speed racing machines.

3.title: Quake, Rattle and Roll

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: Kevin and Grant build a homemade hydrofoil capable of hitting top speeds. Can they make it go so fast it glides over the water? The guys also learn if you can cook a steak with music, and whether they can build a table that can withstand an earthquake.

4.title: Quicksand Quagmire

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: The guys engineer a plan to survive a three-story fall without a parachute, try to escape the legendary powers of homemade quicksand, and build a massive squirt gun from recycled items in the garage.

5.title: Armored Car Combat

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: Kevin and Grant outfit cars with armor and weapons and face off in a no-holds-barred demolition derby. Later, they build a lie detector and to see who's best at playing fast with the truth, and a chainsaw-powered chairlift takes them to great heights.

6.title: Motorcycle Chariots

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

6.plot: The guys turn chariots into speed demons by replacing horses with powerful motorcycles. Kevin and Grant find out what it takes to escape from Alcatraz, and they build the an air hockey table so big you can stand in the rink.

7.title: Rock 'Em Sock 'Em Revenge

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

7.plot: Kevin and Grant build supersized Rock 'Em Sock 'Em Robots and face off in a no-holds-barred battle royale. They'll also find out if they can build a motorcycle with just one wheel, and what it takes to survive the perfect storm.

8.title: USS Scrapyard Submarine

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

8.plot: Kevin and Grant build a submarine and see if they can survive at the bottom of a pool, supersize wind-up cars, and see if you can use duct tape to stop a bullet.

1.title: Trash Can Rocketeers

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

1.plot: Things get explosive when Kevin & Grant push the physics of flight to build the ultimate Trash Can Rocket! TV parts, the Sun's power and ingenuity produce a Solar Powered Death Ray. Fenders bend when the guys try to execute a perfect Power Slide.

2.title: Concrete Canoe Challenge

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

2.plot: Kevin & Grant attempt to reach 30mph riding an improvised Rocket Skateboard! A Catapult built from scraps gets dialed it in for a basketball shooting competition - Man vs Machine. Kevin is convinced the power of buoyancy will float a 400lb Concrete Canoe.

3.title: Homemade Hovercraft Hijinks

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

3.plot: Kevin & Grant test their skills when building a Homemade Hovercraft capable of crossing land and sea. How can a Merry-Go-Round produce Top Gun G-forces? Add motorcycle muscle. The guys attempt to defy gravity and walk on the ceiling in Magnetic Boots.

4.title: Lawnmower Jousting Royale

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

4.plot: While exploring the principles of armor design Grant & Kevin challenge each other to Lawnmower Jousting for backyard glory. Competition is fierce in the inaugural mini-weapon Olympiad. The guys attempt a water, shock and bullet resistant Cell Phone Case.

5.title: In-Human Slingshot

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

5.plot: Kevin & Grant hit the streets to make the fastest Motorized Trike! They turn a childhood game into a risky test of distance and accuracy with their Uber Water Slide. The rapid-fire action of a Meatball Gatling Gun takes culinary arts to a new level.

6.title: Backyard Volcano Blowup

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

6.plot: Kevin & Grant try to survive a 30mph ride through rough terrain in their Off-Road Soap Box Racers. The classic homemade Volcano gets supersized into a 3-stage eruption. Aerodynamics and a 46-year old gridiron record are challenged by a Football Cannon.

7.title: Jumbo Paper Plane

episode of.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong? (TV Series 2015– )

7.plot: Grant and Kevin soar to new heights with a Giant Paper Airplane that can fly over two hundred yards! They try to stop a moving car with no brakes using their James Bond Car Brake. And they use pneumatics to create the Ultimate Beer Delivery.

imdb.title: What Could Possibly Go Wrong?
plot: Two men attempt some of the craziest acts in science to determine if they are possible or not.
